===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|p}} – original meaning uncertain:

* The original form of {{och-l|戣|tr=*gwri}} (a type of [[halberd]]);
* The original form of {{och-l|葵|tr=*gwi}} ([[mallow]]);
* A measuring tool, conceptually related to {{och-l|揆|tr=*gwiʔ}} and {{och-l|季|tr=*kwis}}. {{zh-ref|Cheng (2024)}} proposes it depicts a setup for measuring solar shadows (using {{l|zh|土圭|t=clay measuring rule}}) to determine directions and solstices, and also considers it the original form of {{och-l|規|t=compass; rule|tr=*kwe}}.

